  "eventMetadata": {
    "context_description": "Mexico enters the 2026 FIFA World Cup opener against South Africa at Estadio Azteca as overwhelming favorites, driven by home advantage at altitude, superior recent form with an undefeated run in eight matches, and a stronger squad featuring players like Ra\u00fal Jim\u00e9nez and Juli\u00e1n Qui\u00f1ones. South Africa's return to the tournament after 16 years positions them as clear underdogs facing a motivated co-host side eager to claim three points in Group A. The market's near-certain pricing on Mexico reflects this gap in quality, preparation, and crowd support. Realistic challenges remain limited but could include disciplined defensive displays from Bafana Bafana, opportunistic set-piece threats, or any late injury disruptions that alter lineups.",
